target: research
validations:
  - name: start_research
    type: agent_validation
    severity: error
    args:
      rubric: >
        Verify that the player can start a research project. Opening the
        research tab in the sidebar should display available research nodes
        with their names, costs, and descriptions. Clicking an affordable
        node should start research, deduct the cost from money, and show a
        progress indicator. Nodes the player cannot afford should be grayed
        out and not clickable.
  - name: research_completes
    type: agent_validation
    severity: error
    args:
      rubric: >
        Verify that research completes after the required duration and
        applies its effect. Start a research node and wait for it to finish
        (or fast-forward with speed controls). When complete, the node
        should show as completed in the research tab. The effect should be
        applied — for example, Efficient Feeding should reduce food costs,
        visible as a decrease in per-tick expenses.
  - name: one_at_a_time
    type: agent_validation
    severity: error
    args:
      rubric: >
        Verify that only one research can be active at a time. While a
        research node is in progress, attempting to start another should
        fail or not be offered as an option. The currently active research
        should show its progress bar advancing. After completion, the
        player should be able to start a different node.
